message.text:
#Hiragana Master
Say it Together! Basic Japanese Words in Japanese Alphabetical Order
Today's Word is "TA" TAKE 　#nihongo　#bamboo
日本の単語を五十音順にわかりやすく紹介！「た」け

"Take" (bamboo) is firmly embedded in the Japanese culture, and it is even in the old Japanese famous story, The Tale of the Bamboo-Cutter.Flowering in bamboos occurs in an interval of 10 to 120 years depending on the species, so if you see its flower, the fortune may come to you!?

「竹」は日本文化でとても身近な植物で、昔の物語にも『竹取物語』というお話まであります！実は花も咲きますが、10年～120年に１度しか咲かないので、もし見かけたら幸せになれるかも！？

message.text:
When a swallow flits low, when a cat washes its face, when the moon has a ring around it....
According to Japanese traditions, it is said it will rain when these happen.

Since we are in the middle of Rainy Season Break (meaning sunny today!), these situation didn't happen yesterday？？
Do you have any traditions (superstitions) related to "Rain" in your country too?

「ツバメが低く飛んだら、猫が顔を洗ったら、月に傘がかかったら・・・雨になる！」あなたの国でも「雨」にまつわる言い伝え、ありますか？
http://words.marugotoweb.jp/search_detail.php?id=1114&p=1&q=雨&source=search&lang=en

message.text:
#Hiragana Master
Say it Together! Basic Japanese Words in Japanese Alphabetical Order
Today's Word is "SO" SORA　#nihongo
日本の単語を五十音順にわかりやすく紹介！「そ」ら
http://words.marugotoweb.jp/search_detail.php?id=1652%2C566&p=1&q=sora&source=search&lang=en

Do you know the word "Sora Moyou"（そらもよう、空模様, literally "Sky Pattern") ?? It means "weather (condition)" or "the look of sky", which is often used when the weather looks like going bad. How's weather in your are today?今日の空模様はどうですか？東京の空模様は雨になりそうです。
